data.enText: a sports event that has been arranged to take place on a particular date and at a particular place
data.chText: （定期定点举行的）体育活动，体育节
定于星期六与利物浦队的比赛
这个季度的体育活动项目表

data.enText: a thing such as a bath/ bathtub or a toilet that is fixed in a house and that you do not take with you when you move house
data.chText: 固定设施（如房屋内安装的浴缸或抽水马桶）

data.enText: The price of the house includes fixtures and fittings .
data.chText: 房屋价格包括固定装置和附加设备。

data.enText: He has stayed with us so long he seems to have become a permanent fixture .
data.chText: 他在我们这里待了很久，好像成了我们的固定成员。

simple_means.memory_skill: fix v.固定 + -ture 状态,行为

means: 固定设施(如房屋内安装的浴缸或抽水马桶)
(定期定点举行的)体育活动，体育节

tr: the act of putting something in working order again
an object firmly fixed in place (especially in a household)
the quality of being fixed in place as by some firm attachment

example: a bum who is a Central Park fixture

example.ex: ...a detailed list of what fixtures and fittings are included in the purchase price.
example.tran: 房屋购买价中包括的固定装置及设备的详细清单

value.def: Fixtures are pieces of furniture or equipment, for example baths and sinks, which are fixed inside a house or other building and which stay there if you move.
value.tran: (房间等建筑物内的)固定装置，固定设施

example.ex: City won this fixture 3-0 last season.
example.tran: 上个赛季曼城队在该项赛事中以3比0获胜。

value.def: A fixture is a sports event which takes place on a particular date.
value.tran: (定期举行的)体育活动，体育赛事

example.ex: She was a fixture in New York's nightclubs...
example.tran: 她是纽约夜总会的常客。

example.ex: The cordless kettle may now be a fixture in most kitchens.
example.tran: 无绳电热水壶现在可能是多数厨房的固定设备。

value.def: If you describe someone or something as a fixture in a particular place or occasion, you mean that they always seem to be there.

partsOfSpeech.dec: past- 喂养,牧羊人 + -ture 状态,行为
